In the sequencer, the reduction sequencer will not generate sequence for entries with entry id > 0. If a simple reduction instruction queued in such entries and is a {{singleUop}}, then the {{csid}} will not be set by reduction sequencer.

The fix is to assign the csid (stores mask id offset, a.k.a midOfst) to it when the entry is ready to issue, just like the bypassed simple reduction uop does.



